      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a genus containing birds of prey characterized by thin, tapered wings that enable them to fly at high speed and to change direction rapidly, plumes called "flags" on their legs, and a notch in their hooked beak called a "tooth."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
